Veteran actress, Mary Makgatho dies Published: 07 August 2017 Written by Online Writer Share on Facebook View Comments ANOTHER loss for Mzansi&#39;s entertainment industry. Veteran actress, Mary Makgatho has died. Makgatho died of medical complications after spending weeks in hospital. The actress was known for her roles in Yizo Yizo, Generations, Rhythm City and e.tv&#39;s eKasi: Our Stories. Speaking to TshisaLIVE, Makgatho&#39;s casting manager, Carlynn de Waal-Smit said: &quot;It&#39;s true I just got off the phone with her sister Rose, who confirmed that she passed away. Mary was admitted into high care on 10 July after injuring herself after she fell.&quot; Stars that Mzansi has lost in 2017: JOE MAFELA, IKO MASH, GUNMAN, LUNDI, THANDI KLAASEN, NICK DURANDT,DUMI MASILELA, RAY PHIRI View the discussion thread. blog comments powered by DISQUS back to top Google Tweet Pin it Tweet Next